## 🚀 Quick Start

### Option 1: Automated Setup
```bash
cd "c:\Users\HP\Desktop\New folder (2)\gitops-k8s-gcp"
bash setup.sh
```

### Option 2: Manual Setup
```bash
# 1. Configure GCP
gcloud config set project YOUR_PROJECT_ID
gcloud services enable compute.googleapis.com container.googleapis.com

# 2. Configure Terraform
cd terraform
cp terraform.tfvars.example terraform.tfvars
# Edit terraform.tfvars with your project ID

# 3. Provision infrastructure
terraform init
terraform apply

# 4. Get cluster credentials
gcloud container clusters get-credentials gitops-cluster --region us-central1 --project YOUR_PROJECT_ID

# 5. Run Ansible setup
cd ../ansible
ansible-playbook -i inventory.ini setup-cluster.yml

# 6. Deploy application
cd ..
kubectl apply -f argocd/github-credentials.yaml
kubectl apply -f argocd/gitops-app.yaml
```

### Option 3: Local Development
```bash
# Test locally with Docker Compose
docker-compose up

# Frontend: http://localhost:3001
# Backend API: http://localhost:3000
```

